This is the GingaNCL project. It uses all libraries from NCL 3.0,
GingaCC, TeleMidia Links and TeleMidia Util projects to orchestrate an
NCL presentation.

The autogen.sh script does all the magic calls to automake/autoconf and
friends that are needed to configure the compiling environment.

DEPENDENCIES
============
-> libtool  >= 1.3.4
-> autoconf >= 2.13
-> automake >= 1.4
-> telemidia-util-cpp >= 0.11.2
   (http://svn.softwarepublico.gov.br/trac/ginga/browser/telemidia-util-cpp)
-> ncl30 (from ncl30-cpp) >= 0.11.2
   (http://svn.softwarepublico.gov.br/trac/ginga/browser/ncl30-cpp)
-> ncl30-converter (from ncl30-cpp) >= 0.11.2
   (http://svn.softwarepublico.gov.br/trac/ginga/browser/ncl30-cpp)
-> gingacc-system (from gingacc-cpp) >= 0.11.2
   (http://svn.softwarepublico.gov.br/trac/ginga/browser/gingacc-cpp)
-> gingacc-cm (from gingacc-cpp) >= 0.11.2
   (http://svn.softwarepublico.gov.br/trac/ginga/browser/gingacc-cpp)
-> gingacc-ic (from gingacc-cpp) >= 0.11.2
   (http://svn.softwarepublico.gov.br/trac/ginga/browser/gingacc-cpp)
-> gingacc-contextmanager (from gingacc-cpp) >= 0.11.2
   (http://svn.softwarepublico.gov.br/trac/ginga/browser/gingacc-cpp)
-> gingacc-player (from gingacc-cpp) >= 0.11.2
   (http://svn.softwarepublico.gov.br/trac/ginga/browser/gingacc-cpp)

INSTALLATION
============
As mentioned above, autogen.sh does all the `configure' magic.
So the installation steps are:
 * $ ./autogen.sh
   $ make
   $ make install
If you need to customize any path or regular `configure' value, please
refer to the INSTALL file.
